 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic>π</italic>(
 <italic>t</italic>) ≥ 0. Obviously, the basic SIR model is a special case with no intervention in place, 
 <italic>π</italic>(
 <italic>t</italic>)≡1. In general, the 
 <italic>π</italic>(
 <italic>t</italic>) may be specified by a practitioner to reflect a particular control measure. For an example of the COVID‐19 in Hubei Province, China, a possible choice of 
 <italic>π</italic>(
 <italic>t</italic>) given in the following is a step function that reflects government‐initiated macroisolation measures: 
