 </disp-formula> When 
 <italic>π</italic>
 <sub>0</sub>=(
 <italic>π</italic>
 <sub>01</sub>,
 <italic>π</italic>
 <sub>02</sub>,
 <italic>π</italic>
 <sub>03</sub>,
 <italic>π</italic>
 <sub>04</sub>) are chosen with different values, as shown in Figure 
 <xref rid="insr12402-fig-0010" ref-type="fig">10(A)</xref>–(C), we obtain different types of transmission rate modifiers. Alternatively, 
 <italic>π</italic>(
 <italic>t</italic>) can be a continuous function, say, 
 <math id="nlm-math-54">
  <mi>π</mi>
  <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
