 </math>, that reflects steadily increased community‐level surveillance and personal protection (wearing face masks and washing hands) as shown in Figure 
 <xref rid="insr12402-fig-0010" ref-type="fig">10(D)</xref>–(F). Note that this modifier function does not have to be a monotonic decreasing function and may take a U‐shape to capture the relaxation of control measures. With such a modelling framework, one can carry out comparisons of different preventive protocols via the resulting projected infection risk 
 <italic>θ</italic>
